---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead 
      title="Our Story | Youngish Nomads" 
      description="Meet John and Erica — a Kansas City couple who became empty nesters and decided to see the world while staying youngish at heart." 
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />

    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-hero-inner">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who we are</p>
        <h1>John & Erica. One kid launched.<br/>Infinite possibilities.</h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-body">
      <div class="about-inner">

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>The only thing consistant in life is change</h2>
           <p>
    It actually hit us a year before the graduation cap went in the air — standing in a 
    college dormitory during our daughter's first campus visit, looking at each other with 
    that unspoken realization: this is really happening.
  </p>
  <p>
    The truth is, the transition happens gradually. Teenagers do what teenagers are supposed 
    to do — they pull away, fill their lives with friends and school and their own story. 
    You cheer them on while quietly doing the math on what comes next.
  </p>
  <p>
  We're writing this because we know we're not alone in it. Our daughter still lives 
  at home for now — but the dynamic has shifted, the countdown is real, and the 
  next chapter is closer than it's ever been. The mix of pride and "now what?" 
  is already setting in. If any of that sounds familiar, you're in the right place. 
  This is our story, but we want to hear yours too.
</p>
          <p>
            For a lot of people, that question feels like a loss. For us, it felt like a starting gun.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
            <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    We're John and Erica, based in the Kansas City area. John works in IT by day 
    and is building something of his own on the side — a collection of digital projects 
    fueled by the quiet ambition to one day untether from the desk entirely. 
    Erica brings years of healthcare experience and a grounded, practical perspective 
    that keeps the whole operation honest.
  </p>
  <p>
  John has been a runner for years and travel has always been part of his DNA. 
  Erica is newer to the travel bug — but it's biting. We love our daughter and 
  are soaking up every moment we still have with her at home. But we're also 
  at a stage in life where we're rediscovering each other, dreaming a little 
  bigger, and starting to plan what the next chapter looks like — one trip 
  at a time.
</p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>Why "Youngish Nomads?"</h2>
          <p>
            We're not twenty-something backpackers living out of hostels. But we're not 
            ready for a cruise ship itinerary either. We're somewhere in the middle — 
            experienced enough to travel smart, young enough in spirit to still take the 
            road less traveled.
          </p>
          <p>
            "Nomads" is a little aspirational for now — we still have jobs, a mortgage, 
            and a very real life in Missouri. But the goal? Walk away from corporate America, 
            see the world, and build something that funds the adventure. We're honest about 
            where we are and transparent about where we're headed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block">
          <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
          <ul class="about-list">
            <li>🌍 Honest travel stories — the good, the expensive, and the unexpected</li>
            <li>✈️ Destination guides written for people who aren't 25 anymore</li>
            <li>💪 Staying active and healthy on the road</li>
            <li>💸 The real cost of travel and how we make it work</li>
            <li>🧭 The bigger journey — building a life that doesn't wait for retirement</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="about-block highlight-block">
          <h2>Coming up for us</h2>
          <p>
  First up — Ireland. We're taking our daughter on a graduation trip to celebrate 
  everything she's accomplished, and honestly, to make one more incredible memory 
  together before this chapter closes. It feels like the perfect way to mark the moment. 
  Follow along and we'll take you with us.
</p>
          <a href="/blog" class="btn">Follow Our Journey</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: var(--cream);
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
  }

  .about-hero-inner {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #A8C5A0;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--cream);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .about-body {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--cream);
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3.5rem;
  }

  .about-block h2 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-block p {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .about-list li {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--forest);
  }

  .highlight-block {
    background: var(--forest);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: var(--cream);
  }

  .highlight-block h2 {
    color: #A8C5A0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .highlight-block p {
    color: #C8D8C4;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--brown);
    color: var(--cream);
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--brown-light);
    color: var(--cream);
  }
</style>